From Frank Ball Subject Re Type spesifications CB, VFR, GT, etc VIDAR OLAF SOLBERG wrote Can somebody tell me what all the letter spesifications on motorcycle models really mean Example What means the C, the B and the R in Honda CBR Or the V, S, G, L and P in Suzuki VS GLP Honda a V designates a V engine street bike VF for V , VT for V twin CB is a street bike with an parallel twin or inline cylinder engine R used to mean race bike, but is now also used to mean sport bike CL was for the old steet scramblers street bikes with high pipes CM was a custom street bike CR is dirt only two strokes XL is dual purpose bike XR was dirt only four stroke, but now can be a dual purpose bike if it has an L as a suffix GL is a touring bike Frank Ball UR M work, Hewlett Packard fax, home Valley House Drive IT , XT , Seca , ' F , PL Rohnert Park CA KC WUG, LAW, AMA, Dod , I'm the NRA